# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Docker build-context exclude list for the backend image.
#
# WHY this file exists: `docker build` uploads the whole backend/ directory to
# the daemon as the "build context". Anything not needed to build the jar just
# makes that upload slower and risks busting layer caches (or leaking local
# junk into the image). We keep the context lean and deterministic.
#
# Note: the Dockerfile copies only .mvn/, mvnw, pom.xml and src/ explicitly, so
# most of this is belt-and-braces — but it also protects `COPY . .` patterns a
# future edit might introduce, and keeps context uploads small.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Build output — always regenerated inside the image; never ship the host's copy.
target/

# Local IDE / editor state — irrelevant to the build.
.idea/
*.iml
*.iws
*.ipr
.vscode/
.settings/
.project
.classpath
.factorypath

# Docker + VCS metadata — not part of the application build.
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
Dockerfile
.dockerignore

# Docs and OS cruft.
README.md
HELP.md
.DS_Store
